org.openimaj.image.processor

Interface Processor<I extends Image<?,I>>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - Type of Image
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    GridProcessor<T,I>, ImageProcessor<I>, Inpainter<IMAGE>, KernelProcessor<Q,I>, SinglebandImageProcessor<T,S>, SinglebandKernelProcessor<T,I>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFMMInpainter, AbstractImageMaskInpainter, AbstractLocalThreshold, AdaptiveLocalThresholdBernsen, AdaptiveLocalThresholdContrast, AdaptiveLocalThresholdGaussian, AdaptiveLocalThresholdMean, AdaptiveLocalThresholdMedian, AnisotropicDiffusion, AverageBoxFilter, BasicBackgroundSubtract, BicubicInterpolation, BilinearInterpolation, BrightnessClusteringTransform, CannyEdgeDetector, CannyEdgeDetector2, CLConvolve2D, CLImageProcessor, Close, CompassOperators.Compass0, CompassOperators.Compass135, CompassOperators.Compass45, CompassOperators.Compass90, DifferenceOfGaussian, Dilate, DioramaEffect, Disk, EfrosLeungInpainter, EqualisationProcessor, Erode, FConvolution, FDiscGausConvolve, FFastGaussianConvolve, FGaussianConvolve, FImageBackgroundLearner, FImageConvolveSeparable, FixedResizeProcessor, FourierConvolve, FourierCorrelation, FSobelMagnitude, FSobelX, FSobelY, FTriangleFilter, Gaussian2D, HitAndMiss, Laplacian3x3, LaplacianOfGaussian2D, LiuSamarabanduTextExtractorBasic, LiuSamarabanduTextExtractorMultiscale, LocalContrastFilter, MaskedRobustContrastEqualisation, MaxFilter, MeanCenter, MedianFilter, MinFilter, Open, OrientedPolygonExtractionProcessor, OtsuThreshold, PiecewiseMeshWarp, PolygonExtractionProcessor, RemapProcessor, ResizeProcessor, SequentialThin, SimplePyramid, Skeleton, SkewCorrector, StrokeWidthTransform, SumBoxFilter, SUSANEdgeDetector, TeleaInpainting, TextExtractor, Thicken, Thin

    public interface Processor<I extends Image<?,I>>
    Processor is the super (marker) interface for ImageProcessors, KernelProcessors and PixelProcessors. It is not intended that you create classes implementing this interface directly; rather you should implement one of ImageProcessor, KernelProcessor or PixelProcessor.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
